<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content= "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"> 
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/semantic-ui@2.4.2/dist/semantic.min.css">
  </head>
  <body onLoad="ready()">
    <div class="ui grid doubling stackable container centered">
      <div class="eight wide column centered">
        <h1>What is Evan's blood sugar?</h1>
          <h2><%= guessPhrase %></h2>
          <h3><em><%= commentPhrase %></em></h3>
          <div id="bg-container" class="ui massive right labeled input">
              <input type="number" id="bg" min="40" max="400"/>
              <div class="ui label">
                mg/dL
              </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ui negative message hidden" id="enter-a-bg">
            <p>Oopsies!  Please enter a blood sugar between 40 and 400 mg/dL before guessing!</p>
          </div>
          
          <button onClick="check()" class="ui massive right labeled icon button" id="submit-btn">
              <i class="arrow right icon"></i>
              Guess!
          </button>
          <small>Hint: The answer is between 40 and 400 mg/dL, inclusive.</small>
          <div class="ui icon message hidden" id="result-container">
            <i id="result-icon" class="icon"></i>
            <div class="content">
              <h1 id="score" class="inline"></h1><h4 class="inline">/100</h4>
              <h3 id="result"></h3>
              <div class="ui progress" data-value="0" id="guess-accuracy">
                  <div class="bar">
                    <div class="progress"></div>
                  </div>
              </div>
              <h4 id="hint"></h4>
              <h4 id="correct-notice">Within the next 5 minutes, Evan will have a new blood sugar and you can play again!</h4>
              <p id="high-info">For Evan, <span id="bg"></span> mg/dL is a high blood sugar.  <a href="https://www.jdrf.org/t1d-resources/about/symptoms/high-blood-sugar/">Learn more about high blood sugar.</a></p>
              <p id="normal-info">For Evan, <span id="bg"></span> mg/dL is normal.  Woohoo!</p>
              <p id="low-info">For Evan, <span id="bg"></span> mg/dL is a low blood sugar.  <a href="https://www.jdrf.org/t1d-resources/about/symptoms/low-blood-sugar/">Learn more about low blood sugar.</a></p>
              <small id="info-disclaimer">This isn't medical advice, just commentary.</small>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ui warning message hidden" id="rate-limit-container">
            <p>Slow down, please.  Take the time to ponder your next guess!</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ui icon info message hidden" id="no-data-container">
            <i class="icon frown outline"></i>
            <div class="content">
              <h1>No data</h1>
              <p>We can't check your guess because Evan's latest blood sugar isn't available.  Check back in a couple hours.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ui message">
            <h1>FAQ</h1>
            <p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <h4>What is type one diabetes?</h4>
                  <p>Type one diabetes (T1D) is an autoimmune disease.  In people with T1D, the body has mistakenly killed most of the cells in 
                  the pancreas that produce insulin.  We're left to do what our pancreases canâ€™t, and thatâ€™s no easy task.  
                  Each day, we run a crazy dance of fingerstick blood sugar checks, carbohydrate counting, and insulin doses.
                  <a href="https://www.jdrf.org/t1d-resources/about/">Learn more.</a></p>
                </li><br />
                <li>
                  <h4>How can I help?</h4>
                  <p>Here's a few ways you can learn more about type one diabetes and support type one diabetes research to find a cure:</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li><a href="http://bit.ly/TeamEvan2019guess">Support Evan in the 2019 JDRF One Walk to Cure Diabetes</a></li>
                    <li>Ask a friend who lives with type one diabetes to tell you about it</li>
                    <li><a href="https://www.jdrf.org/impact/advocacy/insulin-access/">Support efforts to lower insulin prices in the US</a></li>
                  <ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
